  PROPIC: "When I was working in Malaysia",
  WELCOME: "If you are facing emotional difficulties, stress, relationship challenges, confusion about life, or simply want to explore yourself in depth, counselling can provide a safe space where you can gently explore your inner world. Hi, you can call me Perry. I'm based in Edinburgh, Scotland. I provide in-person/online counselling & psychotherapy in English, Cantonese or Mandarin mainly for clients based in the UK and HK. I am also a Social Dreaming (SD) host, and I host SD matrix regularly in London.",
  CORETITLE: "my core value",
  CORE1: "I do not heal. Healing occurs when we are “being” together. So I will be your companion on this journey. Rather than pathologising, I see symptoms as psychic expressions of each individual with unique stories, experiences, personalities, behavioural patterns, complexes, psyches, and souls. They encompass a symbolic meaning that can guide our path of individuation.",
  CORE2: "Something might not make sense at the moment, but I believe that the unconscious always moves ahead of us. I am committed to creating a safe container for both of us to journey into depth — to “let it rain, let the wind blow, let the waters flow and the fire burn. Let each thing have its development, let becoming have its day” (<em>The Red Book</em>, C. G. Jung).",
  JOURNEYTITLE: "journey",
  JOURNEY1: "As a therapist, I have spent (and continue spending) years practising, not how to psychoanalyse people, but how to listen with a genuine heart, how to look into people’s eyes with an authentic soul, how to be a mundane human being in relation to the <em>Anima Mundi</em>.",
  JOURNEY2: "I am on the road (and will always be), both physically and symbolically. Where is it leading me to? It is neither a place nor a destination. It is a constant process of becoming, journeying, thinking, imagining, dreaming, writing, drawing, travelling, worlding and bodying... I am lost for words... well, this road takes us to where no words suffice. It is a road to wisdom, to the Philosopher's Stone, to myths, to the archaic, to wholeness. If you are journeying with me, let both of us simmer into ourselves in the alchemical cauldron.",
