  EXP: "Many people who seek psychotherapy have experienced difficulties in childhood or within family relationships. These early experiences may later show up as emotional distress, relationship difficulties, or inner conflicts. In therapy, we work together to gradually understand and transform these experiences, emotions, and patterns. I specialise in early relational trauma, including childhood abuse, neglect, and developmental wounds. I also work with clients from diverse backgrounds on a range of emotional and mental health concerns, including:",
