  APPTITLE1: "Approach",
  APP1: "I do not have an approach, yet I do.",
  APP2_1: "Having trained in psychodynamic and person-centred approaches as my foundation, my practice (and my being) has been profoundly influenced by ",
  APP2_2: "Jungian ",
  APP2_3: "and ",
  APP2_4: "Deleuzo-Guattarian ",
  APP2_5: "thought. I hold these theories to ground, while at the same time, moving beyond them — having no approach at all — allowing both of us  to move freely and creatively. Yes, this is a paradox.",
  APP2_6: "My (non-)approach is informed by various therapeutic frameworks and philosophies. Yet in the consulting room, I let them fall away and return to what is paramount and fundamental: our authentic soul-to-soul encounter.",
  JUNGINTRO: "Carl Jung (1875–1961), Swiss psychiatrist and psychoanalyst. Jungian work, through the exploration of psychic material, emphasises the integration of the conscious and unconscious in order to facilitate growth and transformation — the process of becoming our balanced, true and whole self.",
  DELEUZEINTRO: "Gilles Deleuze (1925-1995), French philosopher, & Félix Guattari (1930-1992), French psychoanalyst. Like mushrooms and their mycelium (i.e., “roots”), their thinking challenges and moves beyond structures and fixed identities to possibilities — to the “becoming something new and unexpected.” This creative relating occurs in the act, in the non-linear process, in the “becoming”, fostering transformation.",
