  APPTITLE2: "How it works",
  APP3: "Psychotherapy, in my opinion, is not about fixing something. It's two people sitting together in dialogue, not only trying to make sense of emotional distress, dysfunctional thoughts, or behaviours, but also — and more importantly — allowing the unconscious to guide us and act upon us. We surrender and listen to the inner wise old man/woman, the spirit, the God within.",
  APP4: "The unconscious communicates through symbols and archetypes. In our work, we explore these using images, stories, dreams, and sandplay within the relational field between us. Together, we catch the wave of the unconscious.",
  APPTITLE3: "The Not-knowing",
  APP5_1: "Midway upon the journey of our life",
  APP5_2: "I found myself within a forest dark,",
  APP5_3: "For the straightforward pathway had been lost.",
  APP5_4: "Ah me! how hard a thing it is to say",
  APP5_5: "What was this forest savage, rough, and stern,",
  APP5_6: "Which in the very thought renews the fear.",
  APP6: "— Inferno, Canto I, Dante Alighieri",
  APP7: "Imagine both of us trying to map a dark, misty forest with a compass. It could be an abyss of darkness, a fathomless realm, far beyond our capacity to understand. We get lost, find a way, get lost again, progress, and regress once more. We are moving together in this purgatorial spiral — deeper and deeper.",
